📘 The core idea

LCES is an educational system.
It is not built to replace judgment.
It is built to improve organization, clarity, and procedural discipline.

Because many legal problems do not begin with weak claims.
They begin earlier — with scattered facts, unstable records, and unclear posture.

That is the problem LCES is built to solve.

